{
  "doc_id": "38167",
  "text": "In Functional Annotation of the mammalian genomes 4 (FANTOM4), an international collaborative research project, we focused on the differentiation process of a human myeloid leukemia cell line to deepen the understanding of the complex layers of the transcriptome and to reverse-engineer the transcriptional regulatory network in a data-driven manner [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . We performed a series of high-throughput experiments using second-generation sequencing together with microarrays to follow the time course of the differentiation process as well as systematic perturbations on a large-scale to characterize the transcriptional regulatory network [CITATION_5] . Furthermore, we addressed the combinatorial roles of transcription factors in human and mouse based on a large-scale *To whom correspondence should be addressed. Tel: +81 45 503 9222; Fax: +81 45 503 9236; Email: kawaji@gsc.riken.jp screening of physical interactions among transcription factors [CITATION_6] . These big data obtained from a wide range of experiments were analyzed individually as well as in combination and published in related but distinct papers while all results are closely connected. We comprehensively provide all our produced data together with detailed annotation to facilitate easy visual inspection and to allow obtaining parts of or the whole data set for global analysis [CITATION_7] . By this, we provide a basis for further experiments and facilitate additional analyses in cellular differentiation. Here we introduce the resource and its update after the initial release.",
